Preconditions:
- The input grid is a valid binary matrix.
- The grid has at least one row and one column.
- The grid has a maximum size of 50x50.
- The grid contains only 0s and 1s.

Postconditions:
- The method returns an integer representing the maximum area of an island in the grid.
- If there is no island in the grid, the method returns 0.
- The method does not modify the input grid.